<task id="UDSS-004" project="UI Dialog Shell Standardization">
  <metadata>
    <title>Extract detectTheme() and parseDataParams() into shared utilities</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>1</phase>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>shared-library, utils</tags>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>P1-foundation</parallel-group>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Consolidate duplicated theme detection and URL parameter parsing logic from multiple solutions into shared utilities. These utilities are required by all Code Page wrappers created in later tasks.</prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer</role>
  <goal>Theme detection and URL param parsing consolidated in @spaarke/ui-components/utils</goal>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Theme detection must support Fluent v9 tokens and dark mode</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/pcf/theme-management.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/webresource/full-page-custom-page.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read existing theme detection implementations in src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/ and src/solutions/EventsPage/</step>
    <step id="2">Consolidate into utils/themeDetection.ts with 4-level cascade: localStorage → URL param → navbar color → system preference</step>
    <step id="3">Create utils/parseDataParams.ts for Xrm data envelope parsing (handles both raw URL params and Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo data encoding)</step>
    <step id="4">Export from utils/index.ts barrel</step>
    <step id="5">Add unit tests for both utilities covering all detection levels and param formats</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Both utilities exported from utils barrel</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests pass for all theme detection levels</criterion>
    <criterion>No duplicated theme/param logic remains across solutions</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
